#: ../../source/fount/04-training-advanced.rst:272
msgid ""
"Fig. 15 shows the proper method to employ if you have to shoot from the "
"prone position (Fig. 16). Incidentally, do not be afraid to adopt this "
"position immediately if circumstances demand it, as might be the case if "
"you had to deal with several adversaries simultaneously. Practice "
"yourself in getting quickly into the prone position, remembering that it "
"gives you the dual advantage of being able to do your shooting from a "
"steady position at a mark which is against the sky-line, as it were, "
"while you yourself offer a less conspicuous target for your opponents "
"than if you were standing up."
msgstr ""

